OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMinister denies donor's    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FAbbott remarks 'race-based'
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A top Tory donor's alleged comments    
OL,6, that Diane Abbott made him "want to    
OL,7, hate all black women" were not         
OL,8, "race-based", a senior minister has    
OL,9, said.                                  
OL,11,FWork and Pensions Secretary Mel Stride 
OL,12,Fsaid Frank Hester's alleged comments   
OL,13,F"were clearly wrong" but argued people 
OL,14,Fshould "move on".                      
OL,16,FMr Hester, who gave the Conservatives  
OL,17,F#10m last year, has apologised for     
OL,18,Fmaking "rude" comments about Ms Abbott.
OL,20,FBut he said his remarks "had nothing to
OL,21,Fdo with her gender nor colour of skin".
